                <h1>When Was McKinsey Founded? Explore the History!</h1>
                <p>McKinsey & Company was founded in 1926 by James O. McKinsey in Chicago, Illinois. It began as a management consulting firm focused on accounting and management practices. Over the years, McKinsey has expanded its expertise into various industries globally, influencing business strategies and corporate vision with its extensive research and analysis.</p>
